       STAGE 2 — PRELIMS FOCUSED
       ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}
    <div id="prelims" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-10);">
      <h2 class="section-heading" style="border-color:#d4a017;">🎯 Stage 2 — Prelims Focused</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted); font-size:var(--text-sm); margin-bottom:var(--space-6);">You know the basics. Now build factual depth, practise elimination, and target the cutoff.</p>

      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap:var(--space-5); margin-bottom:var(--space-6);">
        <div class="strategy-card">
          <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Deepen Every Subject</h4>
          <p class="strategy-card__text">Read all topic notes across <a href="/prelims/" style="color:var(--color-brand); font-weight:600;">10 subjects</a>. Focus on facts, dates, numbers, and schemes — Prelims tests recall, not analysis.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="strategy-card">
          <h4 class="strategy-card__title">PYQ Analysis</h4>
          <p class="strategy-card__text">Solve <a href="/pyq/" style="color:var(--color-brand); font-weight:600;">previous year questions</a> topic-wise. Understand what UPSC asks and where your gaps are. PYQs are the single best prep tool.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="strategy-card">
          <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Current Affairs Daily</h4>
          <p class="strategy-card__text">30-40% of Prelims is current affairs. Use <a href="https://ujiyari.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--color-brand); font-weight:600;">Ujiyari.com</a> daily — news, editorials, and monthly compilations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="strategy-card">
          <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Track &amp; Target Weak Areas</h4>
          <p class="strategy-card__text">Use the <a href="/tracker/" style="color:var(--color-brand); font-weight:600;">Progress Tracker</a> to see which subjects you've covered and which need more work. Aim for 90+ correct on D-day.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

