    {# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       STAGE 3 — MAINS PREPARATION
       ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}
    <div id="mains" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-10);">
      <h2 class="section-heading" style="border-color:#0f4c3a;">✍️ Stage 3 — Mains Preparation</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted); font-size:var(--text-sm); margin-bottom:var(--space-6);">Prelims done or doing both together. You need analytical depth, answer writing practice, and current affairs integration.</p>

      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap:var(--space-5); margin-bottom:var(--space-6);">
        <div class="strategy-card">
          <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Read for Dimensions</h4>
          <p class="strategy-card__text">Mains needs analysis, not facts. Read BharatNotes topic pages for multiple dimensions — social, economic, political, ethical — on every issue.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="strategy-card">
          <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Answer Writing Daily</h4>
          <p class="strategy-card__text">Write 2-3 answers daily. Use the <a href="https://ujiyari.com/mains-guide/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--color-brand); font-weight:600;">Mains Guide</a> I-B-C formula: Introduction → Body → Conclusion with way forward.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="strategy-card">
          <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Editorials Are Mandatory</h4>
          <p class="strategy-card__text">Read <a href="https://ujiyari.com/editorial/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--color-brand); font-weight:600;">editorials on Ujiyari</a> daily — they give you ready-made arguments for GS2/GS3 answers and Essay.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="strategy-card">
          <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Mains PYQ Trends</h4>
          <p class="strategy-card__text">Study <a href="/pyq/" style="color:var(--color-brand); font-weight:600;">Mains PYQ trends</a> — GS2 is moving to case studies, GS3 needs current data, GS4 is 50% case studies.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

